race.comment: PHOENIX LEGEND (2) was beaten just a head at Kembla Grange over 1600m. Improved off a 1.6L defeat there prior over 1300m. Will position forward and with the race fitness he's sure to take beating.  Wary of AMANOAH (5), who has switched from a Victorian yard to Joseph-Jones in Canberra. Started her last campaign in good style beaten just 0.5L over this trip at Cranbourne. Draws awkwardly but should she has the numbers to threaten if presented on-song. Tougher sorting the rest. The local HONEST WARRIOR (1) draws better today and may be the best of them presenting third-up with the blinkers switched for the nose roll. NAMAKA (6) has been racing in Victoria and has switched barns on a 37-day return. Drops back in trip and is likely to run better.
